# Credential vault (INFRA.md) — local mode

> ⚠️ Plaintext secrets. This file is gitignored. Do not commit it.
> Recommended: copy into a password manager (1Password, Bitwarden) for backup.
>
> 🔁 Reuse: when starting a new project, copy connection strings from this
> file directly. The infrastructure does not need re-installation.

Generated: at bootstrap time
Mode: `local` (Compose data services only — no public hosts, no GitOps)

To upgrade to `full` mode (Cloudflare Tunnel + k3s + ArgoCD + Tekton):

1. set `OUTPOST_MODE=full` in `.env`
2. fill `ROOT_DOMAIN`, `CF_TUNNEL_TOKEN`, `GIT_USER`, `GIT_TOKEN`, `MANIFEST_REPO_URL`
3. re-run `bash bootstrap.sh`

